<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 2:48AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Pushmataha County through 315 AM CDT...
At 247 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Tuskahoma, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Clayton...                        Clayton Lake State Park...
Tuskahoma...                      Nashoba...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
